Yes, he has urged us to ...

507
00:44:54,133 --> 00:44:56,795
solve our differences with Washington.

508
00:44:57,303 --> 00:45:02,907
But, sir, the deadline is October.

509
00:45:03,107 --> 00:45:03,996
Can a solution be found by then?

510
00:45:05,144 --> 00:45:07,840
Perhaps. But if we fail...

511
00:45:08,021 --> 00:45:11,539
...if war does come...

512
00:45:11,818 --> 00:45:15,777
...tell me frankly, from the Navy's viewpoint...

513
00:45:15,955 --> 00:45:18,810
...what are our chances against the Americans?

514
00:45:19,826 --> 00:45:22,090
lf we must,

515
00:45:22,328 --> 00:45:24,319
we can raise havoc with them for a year.

516
00:45:24,964 --> 00:45:28,058
After that, l can guarantee nothing.

517
00:45:32,939 --> 00:45:34,133
Mr. Prime Minister,

518
00:45:34,340 --> 00:45:36,535
l hope you will continue the negotiations.

519
00:45:36,775 --> 00:45:37,818
Please remember,

520
00:45:38,177 --> 00:45:40,076
