796
01:08:44,766 --> 01:08:46,199
Captain Wilkinson's.

797
01:08:52,707 --> 01:08:54,197
Did you see the president?

798
01:08:54,442 --> 01:08:58,744
No, l saw Harry Hopkins.

799
01:08:58,880 --> 01:09:01,508
And did he read the whatever it is?

800
01:09:01,749 --> 01:09:03,979
No, he doesn't have the key.

801
01:09:05,653 --> 01:09:08,178
I gave the pouch to our Naval aide, Lieutenant Schulz.

802
01:09:08,389 --> 01:09:10,152
He took it in to the president.

803
01:09:11,292 --> 01:09:13,157
And the president has a key, I suppose?

804
01:09:15,430 --> 01:09:16,692
Of course he has.

805
01:09:17,665 --> 01:09:19,553
And did Lieutenant Schulz say anything?

806
01:09:20,868 --> 01:09:22,324
He said, "Thank you."

807
01:09:22,870 --> 01:09:25,134
Darling, step on it, will you?

808
01:09:32,747 --> 01:09:34,772
lf we can see nothing,

809
01:09:35,016 --> 01:09:36,972
then neither can American patrol planes.

810
01:09:37,418 --> 01:09:39,750
I'm more concerned about a submarine detecting us.

811
01:09:42,724 --> 01:09:46,421
Stand by to load the bombs

812
01:09:46,694 --> 01:09:51,449
repeat  stand by to load the bombs

813
01:09:51,699 --> 01:09:55,567
Dead on schedule.

814
01:10:04,879 --> 01:10:06,835
Admiral Stark can't be reached.

815
01:10:07,215 --> 01:10:09,103
Should l take it to chief of staff?

816
01:10:09,317 --> 01:10:10,249
It's after 10,

817
01:10:10,451 --> 01:10:13,147
General Marshall always retires early.

818
01:10:21,429 --> 01:10:26,128
I see no reason to disturb Marshall with something that's incomplete.

819
01:10:26,601 --> 01:10:30,595
- Wait till you have the final part. - Yes, sir.

820
01:10:31,906 --> 01:10:33,103
lf you're so concerned...

821
01:10:33,390 --> 01:10:36,258
...why don't we call chief of war plans, Admiral Turner?

822
01:10:36,444 --> 01:10:38,400
His telephone doesn't answer, sir.

823
01:10:39,314 --> 01:10:42,543
- You don't happen to know where he is? - No idea.

824
01:10:53,494 --> 01:10:55,655
The president has already discussed it with me.

825
01:10:57,332 --> 01:11:00,460
He sent a personal message to the emperor.

826
01:11:00,768 --> 01:11:03,396
But when the final part of this comes in,

827
01:11:03,571 --> 01:11:04,936
I'd like to see it then.

828
01:11:05,273 --> 01:11:08,262
- Good night, commander. - Good night, sir.

829
01:11:17,785 --> 01:11:20,083
I was starved. I'll bet you are.

830
01:11:20,288 --> 01:11:21,653
Oh, thank you, dear.

831
01:11:25,893 --> 01:11:29,687
Can't you tell me anything?  Even a hint?

832
01:11:34,302 --> 01:11:36,224
You'd think the world was falling apart.

833
01:11:37,538 --> 01:11:39,904
Admiral Stark talked to the president.

834
01:11:40,108 --> 01:11:43,451
What did the president say?

835
01:11:46,381 --> 01:11:49,441
He sent a personal message to the emperor.

836
01:12:19,147 --> 01:12:20,136
Gordy.

837
01:12:20,481 --> 01:12:21,641
yeah

838
01:12:21,849 --> 01:12:25,273
We got those B-1 7s coming in from California in the morning.

839
01:12:25,551 --> 01:12:29,377
Honolulu radio will stay on the air all night... so the planes can home in.

840
01:12:29,590 --> 01:12:32,821
You and l had better be in that control tower at 7:30 sharp.

841
01:12:33,027 --> 01:12:34,877
Yes, sir.

842
01:12:43,871 --> 01:12:47,696
- Tyler, I've got a job for you. - Sir.

843
01:12:47,809 --> 01:12:51,802
Report to the new radar center at Fort Shafter at 0400.

844
01:12:52,180 --> 01:12:53,841
At 4:00 in the morning?

845
01:12:54,082 --> 01:12:55,845
From 4 to 7 a.m.

846
01:12:56,084 --> 01:12:59,178
Our marvel of science only operates for three hours.

847
01:12:59,520 --> 01:13:00,145
Lucky boy.

848
01:13:00,388 --> 01:13:01,878
Lucky boy!

849
01:13:13,734 --> 01:13:15,099
Captain, how's it feel?

850
01:13:15,269 --> 01:13:16,793
First command, first patrol?

851
01:13:17,038 --> 01:13:18,562
Just fine, Mr. Young.

852
01:13:23,111 --> 01:13:25,773
ln fact, l think I'll turn in for a while.

853
01:13:31,786 --> 01:13:33,745
- Good night, sir. - Good night.

854
01:13:42,263 --> 01:13:45,960
The Commander-in-Chief has sent a message...

855
01:13:46,167 --> 01:13:49,159
...wishing us good luck.

856
01:13:49,871 --> 01:13:53,162
That, plus the lmperial Proclamation...

857
01:13:53,341 --> 01:13:58,043
...has undoubtedly stirred your loyalty to the Empire.

858
01:13:59,347 --> 01:14:01,372
The success of this mission...

859
01:14:01,616 --> 01:14:05,245
...depends on surprise. lf we achieve it...

860
01:14:05,586 --> 01:14:09,584
...the code words "Tora, Tora, Tora," will be sent out.

861
01:14:11,192 --> 01:14:13,422
Now that the hour

862
01:14:13,628 --> 01:14:18,258
for battle draws near...

863
01:14:18,405 --> 01:14:20,760
...I will not burden you with the usual pep talk.

864
01:14:21,769 --> 01:14:27,260
Instead I shall hoist the famous "Z" flag...

865
01:14:27,408 --> 01:14:31,833
...beneath which, Commander-in-Chief Togo led his fleet to victory...

866
01:14:32,113 --> 01:14:35,844
...in the historic battle against the Russians.

867
01:14:36,284 --> 01:14:41,415


868
01:14:57,516 --> 01:15:00,816


869
01:15:27,300 --> 01:15:28,289
Here you are.

870
01:15:29,703 --> 01:15:30,431
Kramer.

871
01:15:30,637 --> 01:15:32,525
Al, listen to this.

872
01:15:32,739 --> 01:15:34,263
The 14th part.

873
01:15:34,541 --> 01:15:37,903
"Will the ambassadors please submit our reply...

874
01:15:38,143 --> 01:15:40,771
...to the United States government at precisely 1 p.m...

875
01:15:41,064 --> 01:15:43,065
...December 7th, your time."

876
01:15:43,617 --> 01:15:45,505
1 p.m.?

877
01:15:45,719 --> 01:15:49,246
"Precisely 1 p.m., your time."

878
01:15:50,757 --> 01:15:52,190
I'll be right over.

879
01:16:00,791 --> 01:16:03,291


880
01:16:07,792 --> 01:16:10,292


881
01:16:10,944 --> 01:16:14,107
Look at the president's message. I should have had it hours ago.

882
01:16:14,681 --> 01:16:19,607
As you know, communications have been delayed and frequently garbled lately.

883
01:16:19,819 --> 01:16:21,446
Or deliberately interfered with.

884
01:16:24,958 --> 01:16:28,291
Gene, call the foreign minister.

885
01:16:31,097 --> 01:16:34,487
Tell him l want an immediate audience with the emperor.

886
01:16:38,471 --> 01:16:40,632
Why is this so important?

887
01:16:41,141 --> 01:16:42,870
Does this Roosevelt message say anything new?

888
01:16:52,952 --> 01:16:56,943
It merely proposes a heart-to-heart exchange...

889
01:16:57,023 --> 01:16:59,089
...between the two Chiefs of State.

890
01:16:59,893 --> 01:17:03,158
It could start negotiations afresh.

891
01:17:13,173 --> 01:17:14,868
It's too late for that.

892
01:17:17,143 --> 01:17:20,906
It's just as well the message didn't come a day or two earlier.

893
01:17:24,150 --> 01:17:27,711
What do l tell Ambassador Grew?

894
01:17:28,421 --> 01:17:31,151
You are Foreign Minister!

895
01:17:31,324 --> 01:17:34,976
Report to the palace alone with the message.

896
01:17:39,400 --> 01:17:44,024
"After deciphering...part 14...

897
01:17:46,523 --> 01:17:48,690
...destroy at once...

898
01:17:50,678 --> 01:17:56,601
...your cipher machine...

899
01:17:57,308 --> 01:17:58,909
...all codes...

900
01:18:00,161 --> 01:18:04,485
...and secret documents."

901
01:18:05,793 --> 01:18:07,283
Translate this immediately.

902
01:18:07,495 --> 01:18:10,147
- Give a copy to Kramer when he comes. - Yes, sir.

903
01:18:10,198 --> 01:18:11,825
I've got to get the hell out of here.

904
01:19:32,880 --> 01:19:34,745
Hey, look at this.

905
01:19:35,349 --> 01:19:37,510
Finally got one.

906
01:19:42,356 --> 01:19:43,721
Communication center.

907
01:19:43,925 --> 01:19:44,823
It even works.

908
01:19:45,092 --> 01:19:45,854
That's great.

909
01:19:46,594 --> 01:19:49,085
Opana Point, communications check.

910
01:19:51,098 --> 01:19:52,292
Are you reading us?

911
01:19:52,600 --> 01:19:53,692
Coming in loud and clear.

912
01:19:59,640 --> 01:20:00,766
Where's the general?

913
01:20:00,975 --> 01:20:02,966
It's Sunday, sir.

914
01:20:17,625 --> 01:20:19,183
This is Colonel Bratton.

915
01:20:19,393 --> 01:20:21,452
Connect me with Chief of Staff, General Marshall.

916
01:20:22,630 --> 01:20:24,962
Yes, at his quarters, Fort Myer.

917
01:20:30,137 --> 01:20:32,469
Chief of staff's quarters, Sergeant Aguirre speaking.

918
01:20:34,141 --> 01:20:36,530
Yes, Colonel Bratton.

919
01:20:36,978 --> 01:20:38,900
I'm sorry, sir, the general isn't here.

920
01:20:40,414 --> 01:20:43,303
Where he always is this time Sunday morning.

921
01:21:00,468 --> 01:21:03,426
- Where's Colonel Bratton? - Gone to see General Marshall.

922
01:21:03,738 --> 01:21:05,330
He left this for you, sir.

923
01:21:06,607 --> 01:21:08,165


924
01:21:08,376 --> 01:21:11,038


925
01:21:33,968 --> 01:21:35,799
Where is the Ambassador?

926
01:21:38,906 --> 01:21:41,795
Here is another part of the message, sir.

927
01:21:51,819 --> 01:21:52,979
Mr. Ambassador

928
01:21:53,587 --> 01:21:59,949
We are instructed to submit the message at 1 :00 p.m. today.

929
01:22:01,595 --> 01:22:03,551
One p.m.?

930
01:22:05,599 --> 01:22:08,989
The 14th part of this intercept Kramer just delivered...

931
01:22:09,136 --> 01:22:11,263
...indicates to me the Japanese are going to attack.

932
01:22:13,541 --> 01:22:16,535
None of us doubt war is coming.

933
01:22:16,911 --> 01:22:19,869
We know they have an expeditionary force heading south.

934
01:22:21,349 --> 01:22:24,910
Sir, as hostilities seem imminent...

935
01:22:25,119 --> 01:22:29,137
... l recommend you telephone Admiral Kimmel... in Hawaii.

936
01:22:46,874 --> 01:22:48,205
No.

937
01:22:50,411 --> 01:22:52,504
I better call the president first.

938
01:22:55,349 --> 01:22:57,510
Now, if you'll all please excuse me?

939
01:22:57,718 --> 01:23:00,180
- Yes, sir. - Thank you, sir.

940
01:23:17,705 --> 01:23:25,271


941
01:25:59,467 --> 01:26:00,627
Hurry...

942
01:26:13,948 --> 01:26:18,010
The men are in good spirits, sir.

943
01:26:18,318 --> 01:26:19,540
They are eager to go.

944
01:26:21,245 --> 01:26:26,381
Yes, they are eager because they do not know the taste of battle.

945
01:27:07,635 --> 01:27:09,159
Commander

946
01:27:09,336 --> 01:27:11,600
The mechanics asked me to give you this for good luck

947
01:27:11,839 --> 01:27:13,761
at Pearl Harbor.

948
01:27:37,364 --> 01:27:39,958


949
01:28:27,246 --> 01:28:28,997
Bring her into the wind.

950
01:32:06,298 --> 01:32:09,826
"The Japanese government regrets to have to notify...

951
01:32:09,986 --> 01:32:14,597
the American government...that, in view of the attitude of the American government...

952
01:32:15,176 --> 01:32:18,408
...it is impossible to reach...

953
01:32:18,969 --> 01:32:20,478
...an agreement through negotiations."

954
01:32:21,049 --> 01:32:22,107
Sir?

955
01:32:22,317 --> 01:32:24,308
- There are supplemental messages. - Thank you.

956
01:32:36,698 --> 01:32:37,995
Gentlemen, l am convinced the Japanese intend to attack...

957
01:32:38,199 --> 01:32:42,090
...at or shortly after 1 :00 today.

958
01:32:42,737 --> 01:32:46,332
- I'll alert all Pacific commands. - Yes, sir.

959
01:32:56,050 --> 01:32:57,938
Colonel Bratton, just a minute.

960
01:32:58,309 --> 01:33:00,909
Take this to communications center.

961
01:33:14,803 --> 01:33:15,735
turn around

962
01:33:15,904 --> 01:33:17,166
turn around

963
01:33:18,072 --> 01:33:19,004
Steady

964
01:33:19,240 --> 01:33:20,172
Steady

965
01:33:20,789 --> 01:33:23,403
We will follow that ship into Pearl Harbor.

966
01:33:34,255 --> 01:33:35,347
Come in.

967
01:33:36,180 --> 01:33:38,749
Captain, can you come to the bridge?

968
01:33:38,949 --> 01:33:39,974
Very well.

969
01:33:44,688 --> 01:33:46,290
Sub contact, Mr. Goepner?

970
01:33:46,801 --> 01:33:48,165
- We're not sure. - What ship?

971
01:33:48,236 --> 01:33:49,933
The Navy tug Antares.

972
01:33:51,906 --> 01:33:53,794
Look astern of her, captain.

973
01:33:54,642 --> 01:33:56,405
She's towing a target raft.

974
01:33:56,811 --> 01:33:58,767
Look between the ship and the raft, sir.

975
01:34:08,890 --> 01:34:11,188
That, Mr. Goepner, is a submarine.

976
01:34:11,392 --> 01:34:13,553
She's sneaking through the net into the harbor.

977
01:34:13,795 --> 01:34:14,921
General Quarters.

978
01:34:15,051 --> 01:34:18,125
- Sound General Quarters. - All engines ahead, full.

979
01:34:36,240 --> 01:34:39,909
- Come left 15 degrees. - Come left 15 degrees, sir.

980
01:34:40,244 --> 01:34:43,278
- Tell Antares we're attacking. - Aye, aye, sir.

981
01:34:48,696 --> 01:34:50,584
Flags, tell Antares we're attacking.

982
01:34:58,262 --> 01:35:02,200
- Mount one, commence firing. - Mount one, commence firing.

983
01:35:21,095 --> 01:35:24,523
- Stand by to roll depth charges. - Stand by to roll depth charges.

984
01:35:29,404 --> 01:35:30,693
- Roll one. - Roll one.

985
01:35:39,514 --> 01:35:40,952
- Roll two. - Roll two.

986
01:35:56,097 --> 01:35:57,189
Notify Com-14

987
01:35:57,398 --> 01:36:00,561
we dropped depth charges on a sub in our security zone.

988
01:36:00,824 --> 01:36:01,824
Aye, aye, sir.

989
01:36:21,178 --> 01:36:23,087
Captain Earle speaking.

990
01:36:23,324 --> 01:36:25,155
We have a message from the ward.

991
01:36:25,460 --> 01:36:26,620
All right, read it to me.

992
01:36:27,726 --> 01:36:33,022
"Have dropped depth charges on sub operating in our security zone."

993
01:36:34,316 --> 01:36:37,568
We've had so many of these false sightings, Kaminsky.

994
01:36:37,819 --> 01:36:39,570
But this is the real thing, sir.

995
01:36:39,821 --> 01:36:41,739
Closer than any previous sighting.

996
01:36:41,990 --> 01:36:43,449
Just off the harbor entrance.

997
01:36:44,451 --> 01:36:47,745
You and l know the skipper of that destroyer is a green kid.

998
01:36:47,913 --> 01:36:49,372
I'll pass it to Admiral Block.

999
01:36:49,750 --> 01:36:51,542
With all due respect, sir,

1000
01:36:51,719 --> 01:36:53,982
l think we should alert all commanders.

1001
01:36:54,288 --> 01:36:56,383
Confirmation, Kaminsky.

1002
01:36:56,690 --> 01:36:59,479
I want confirmation.

1003
01:37:22,239 --> 01:37:28,300
The sunburst reminds me of our flag,

1004
01:37:50,517 --> 01:37:52,636
Ed, this is hot.

1005
01:37:53,013 --> 01:37:56,835
General Marshall wants it sent to all commanders by the fastest route.

1006
01:37:56,995 --> 01:37:58,024
Right.

1007
01:38:02,089 --> 01:38:05,081
The generaI's handwriting, it's hard to read.

1008
01:38:07,260 --> 01:38:09,956
You're gonna have to help me with it, Rufe.

1009
01:39:03,674 --> 01:39:06,981
Hey, I'm picking up Honolulu on the radio.

1010
01:39:07,103 --> 01:39:11,745
Check your direction-finder dial.

1011
01:39:12,092 --> 01:39:15,584
It's coming from five degrees to port, sir.

1012
01:39:16,596 --> 01:39:19,121
Okay, keep riding that beam.

1013
01:39:19,299 --> 01:39:20,391
yes sir

1014
01:39:33,092 --> 01:39:36,992


1015
01:39:42,337 --> 01:39:46,006
Major, l picked up some great music from Honolulu.

1016
01:39:46,425 --> 01:39:48,634
That's fine, pipe it through.

1017
01:39:51,722 --> 01:39:53,097
Okay.

1018
01:40:08,071 --> 01:40:10,573
Where's the damn chow truck?

1019
01:40:13,720 --> 01:40:14,914
Shut the thing down, George.

1020
01:40:15,155 --> 01:40:16,850
It's already after 7.

1021
01:40:16,995 --> 01:40:19,421
Hey, Joe, come here.

1022
01:40:19,682 --> 01:40:21,149
What do you make of that?

1023
01:40:21,392 --> 01:40:23,522
I've been watching it for minutes.

1024
01:40:23,919 --> 01:40:25,254
It's moving in, fast.

1025
01:40:25,463 --> 01:40:27,831
I've never seen anything that big.

1026
01:40:27,982 --> 01:40:31,062
- Looks like two main pulses. - Hey, Joe, l got it.

1027
01:40:31,852 --> 01:40:36,096
I make that about 140 miles north, three degrees east.

1028
01:40:36,600 --> 01:40:40,271
Don't make sense, we got no planes out that far.

1029
01:40:40,595 --> 01:40:42,538
We gotta contact the information center.

1030
01:40:42,789 --> 01:40:45,148
Our problem is over at 7:00.

1031
01:40:45,483 --> 01:40:47,980
The center might make some sense out of it.

1032
01:40:48,011 --> 01:40:49,951
Okay, suit yourself.

1033
01:40:59,733 --> 01:41:01,428
lnformation center.

1034
01:41:02,902 --> 01:41:06,133
Yeah? l don't know, Mac, we're all closed down here.

1035
01:41:07,130 --> 01:41:09,340
ls that right?

1036
01:41:09,575 --> 01:41:10,169
Hang on a minute.

1037
01:41:10,391 --> 01:41:11,741
Lieutenant, sir.

1038
01:41:19,219 --> 01:41:20,584
Lieutenant Tyler.

1039
01:41:20,743 --> 01:41:23,244
Sir, this is Private Elliot, Opana Point.

1040
01:41:23,438 --> 01:41:25,788
There's a large formation of planes coming in...

1041
01:41:26,026 --> 01:41:29,120
... 140 miles, three degrees east.

1042
01:41:29,277 --> 01:41:31,127
Yeah?

1043
01:41:31,464 --> 01:41:34,763
Well, don't worry about it.

1044
01:41:37,118 --> 01:41:39,729
The boys at Opana Point must have picked up the B-17s...

1045
01:41:40,372 --> 01:41:41,997
...coming in from the mainland.

1046
01:41:43,875 --> 01:41:47,679
- He said not to worry about it. - Come on, let's go eat.

1047
01:41:55,011 --> 01:41:59,815
Colonel, l sent this to Manila,the canal zone and San Francisco...

1048
01:41:59,983 --> 01:42:03,125
...but the direct channel to Hawaii is out.

1049
01:42:03,361 --> 01:42:04,661
Atmospherics again?

1050
01:42:04,865 --> 01:42:05,889
Yes, sir,

1051
01:42:06,133 --> 01:42:07,498
it's real bad today.

1052
01:42:07,834 --> 01:42:10,200
We could give it to the Navy.

1053
01:42:10,318 --> 01:42:13,100
What makes you think their atmospherics are better?

1054
01:42:15,375 --> 01:42:17,876
- Send it as a telegram. - Yes, sir.

1055
01:42:19,399 --> 01:42:21,999


1056
01:42:25,542 --> 01:42:30,045
Our ultimatum should be delivered in Washington

1057
01:42:30,222 --> 01:42:31,053
before the attack begins.

1058
01:42:33,460 --> 01:42:35,291
I hope everything is on schedule.

1059
01:42:35,302 --> 01:42:37,992
Don't worry, sir. The Emperor insists...

