1261
02:15:55,056 --> 02:15:55,954
Yes, sir.

1262
02:16:03,698 --> 02:16:05,689
Come on...

1263
02:16:17,145 --> 02:16:18,271
Run for it!

1264
02:16:25,920 --> 02:16:28,013
Drop the hose and get the ladders and axes.

1265
02:16:29,724 --> 02:16:30,884
What are you waiting for?

1266
02:16:31,092 --> 02:16:33,518
- We got no water. - Why? What's wrong?

1267
02:16:33,628 --> 02:16:35,988
It's the Arizona. She cut the pipes in the mains.

1268
02:16:36,164 --> 02:16:39,692
The tanker in the ocean there is full of aviation fuel.

1269
02:16:39,767 --> 02:16:41,433
lf it goes, we'll blow up half the harbor.

1270
02:16:41,870 --> 02:16:42,928
Hurry up..

1271
02:16:43,138 --> 02:16:44,196
Come on...

1272
02:16:44,439 --> 02:16:45,565
Get out of here...

1273
02:17:46,234 --> 02:17:47,132
Hey, look out!

1274
02:17:48,136 --> 02:17:50,525
Get out of here

1275
02:18:07,655 --> 02:18:12,080
ln all my 50 years of public service...

1276
02:18:14,162 --> 02:18:16,120
...l have never seen a document so crowded with infamous falsehoods...

1277
02:18:18,443 --> 02:18:20,193
...and distortions...

1278
02:18:20,862 --> 02:18:23,196
...on a scale so huge...

1279
02:18:23,364 --> 02:18:26,366
...that l never imagined until today...

1280
02:18:27,243 --> 02:18:29,870
...that any government on this planet...

1281
02:18:30,079 --> 02:18:32,873
...was capable of uttering them.

1282
02:18:46,494 --> 02:18:48,052
Mr. Hull.

1283
02:18:49,897 --> 02:18:51,330
Go.

1284
02:19:56,464 --> 02:19:58,659
What's the matter? Why in hell doesn't the next wave take off?

1285
