02:22:52,640 --> 02:22:53,595
Yes, all right.

1327
02:22:54,642 --> 02:22:58,134
This came from the decoding room, a cablegram from the War Department.

1328
02:23:11,859 --> 02:23:13,554
Get a copy to Admiral Kimmel.

1329
02:23:31,645 --> 02:23:32,441
Pardon me, admiral.

1330
02:23:32,646 --> 02:23:35,115
- From Washington. - Thank you.

1331
02:23:43,324 --> 02:23:44,256
Gentlemen.

1332
02:23:51,665 --> 02:23:55,489
"The Japanese are presenting at 1 p.m...

1333
02:23:55,529 --> 02:23:57,489
...Eastern Standard Time today...

1334
02:23:58,199 --> 02:24:00,533
...what amounts to an ultimatum.

1335
02:24:02,870 --> 02:24:07,874
Just what significance the hour set may have, we do not know...

1336
02:24:09,919 --> 02:24:12,879
...but be on alert accordingly."

1337
02:24:14,382 --> 02:24:15,882
Signed...

1338
02:24:16,509 --> 02:24:20,845
...George C. Marshall, chief of staff.

1339
02:24:29,939 --> 02:24:31,856
My God.

1340
02:24:47,331 --> 02:24:51,251
This leaves the Navy with only two combat groups in the Central Pacific.

1341
02:24:51,725 --> 02:24:53,716
Ours and the Lexington.

1342
02:24:54,295 --> 02:24:55,990
We don't want to get caught like they did.

1343
02:24:56,230 --> 02:24:57,925
I don't intend to.

1344
02:24:58,399 --> 02:24:59,855
When can you be ready for sea again?

1345
02:25:00,067 --> 02:25:01,557
We can fuel and provision and

1346
02:25:01,735 --> 02:25:03,100
be under way before dawn.

1347
02:25:03,437 --> 02:25:05,701
Good. That's good.

1348
02:25:16,884 --> 02:25:20,706
Here is an announcement from the Navy Department, released December 7th.

1349
02:25:21,789 --> 02:25:26,146
"Before daybreak today, the Imperial Navy successfully launched...

1350
02:25:26,727 --> 02:25:31,220
...a large-scale air raid against the American Pacific Fleet in Hawaii."

1351
02:25:31,765 --> 02:25:33,756
We salute the Commander-in-Chief of our Fleet...

1352
02:25:33,834 --> 02:25:37,380
...Admiral Yamamoto.

1353
02:25:51,655 --> 02:25:57,553
I had intended to deal a fatal blow to the American fleet...

1354
02:25:57,758 --> 02:26:01,154
...by attacking Pearl Harbor...

1355
02:26:01,294 --> 02:26:05,325
...immediately after Japan's official declaration of war.

1356
02:26:07,468 --> 02:26:15,364
But according to the American radio, Pearl Harbor was attacked...

1357
02:26:16,143 --> 02:26:19,340
...55 minutes before our ultimatum...

1358
02:26:19,546 --> 02:26:22,801
...was delivered in Washington.

1359
02:26:26,453 --> 02:26:29,117
I can't imagine anything...

1360
02:26:29,934 --> 02:26:33,724
...that would infuriate the Americans more.

1361
02:26:35,664 --> 02:26:38,319
I fear all we have done...

1362
02:26:38,399 --> 02:26:40,890
...is to awaken a sleeping giant

1363
